  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Abokobi Livestock and Beekeeping Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmer households, Women, Youth</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Theoretical and hands-on training in Beekeeping, grasscutter management, small ruminant and poultry production. Training in project management and record keeping. Training in compost preparation. Training on the 12 HPI cornerstones. Training on gender equity. HIV/AIDS awareness creation. Farmer to farmer visitation.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This Livestock, Beekeeping and Grasscutter project targets 232 families in 13 communities in the Ga district of the Greater Accra Region. The communities are: Abokobi-Hebron, Abooman, Anang Charles, Dravaga, Pantang New town, Sesemi, Sesemi SDA, Abokobi Estate, Pantang old town, Evergreen-Abooman, Nyame Krom, and Ajako Estates. These rural farming communities are characterized by seasonal unemployment, high maternal and child mortality rates, poor nutrition and low incomes. To ensure sustainable community development and resiliency, this project will provide 70 Beehives, 180 grasscutters, 528 goats and 2,320 layer birds, alongside training to 116 families directly and through the Passing on the Gift (POG) process to another 116 families over a 3 year period. The project will also address issues on HIV/AIDS and Gender equity.</narrative>
  </description>
